snippet.textDisplay:
A few observations.

1. It was a game of boys playing against men. The boys were losing their possessions after a couple of passes & missed all their chances to score. The men were very skilled & professional.

2. It was Jose’s tactics to play counter attack in the first 75 minutes & then bring reinforcement in & go after Liverpool with everything he is got. It almost worked but he only had boys who could not finish.

3. Tottenham is much better without Kane & Erickson who though great players, are too slow. The slow game does not benefit Son, Alli, Moura, or the counter attacking game that Jose likes.

4. I could see them selling Harry in the future getting huge funds for him & build the team around Alli, Moura, Son, LoCelso, etc.

5. Liverpool was not at their best due to the tactics of Jose but they still won because they were a better team.
snippet.textOriginal:
A few observations.

1.  It was a game of boys playing against men.  The boys were losing their possessions after a couple of passes & missed all their chances to score.  The men were very skilled & professional.

2.  It was Jose’s tactics to play counter attack in the first 75 minutes & then bring reinforcement in & go after Liverpool with everything he is got.  It almost worked but he only had boys who could not finish.

3.  Tottenham is much better without Kane & Erickson who though great players, are too slow.  The slow game does not benefit Son, Alli, Moura, or the counter attacking game that Jose likes.

4.  I could see them selling Harry in the future getting huge funds for him & build the team around Alli, Moura, Son, LoCelso, etc.

5.  Liverpool was not at their best due to the tactics of Jose but they still won because they were a better team.
